The BixIy were grown by a low-temperature solution technique, as shown in Fig. 1a. First, Bi2O3, I2, and Au were dissolved in a mixed hydroiodic acid and ethanol solution to form precursor solutions. Excessive iodine is used to dissolve gold in hydroiodic acid fully. Then the solution refinement technique was employed to grow high-quality crystals26. Namely, the precursor solutions were pretreated by solvothermal in 1,4-butyrolactone for three times and then refined by hydrothermal for 1-time. Bi3+ was reduced by I− with Au acted as a catalyst during the solution pretreatment; the chemical reactions in the solution were:14H++4I−+O2↑→△2I2↑+2H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
